Column Comment.0: PALEO SUMMARY IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the paleo summary report thatis captured.
Column Comment.1: DETAIL IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for this portion of the detail in the summaryreport.
Column Comment.2: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.3: ANALYSIS IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier assigned to a lab analysis.
Column Comment.4: SOURCE: The source used for this analysis/
Column Comment.5: BASE MEASURED DEPTH: the lower measured depth for this detail record.
Column Comment.7: CLIMATE IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the climate
Column Comment.8: DESCRIPTION: a text based description of this detail.
Column Comment.9: CONFIDENCE IDENTIFER A Unique identifier for the code associated withconfidence of a paleontological event or pick, such as positive, doubtful etc. In somecompanies, numeric codes are assigned.
Column Comment.10: ECOZONE IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for a sedimentary rock unit or environmentin which fossil deposition occurs. Often, these ecozones are marine or fresh water.Marine ecozones include the category of marine benthic zones, namely shelf, slope,and abyssal zones. The ecozone is defined by the organisms that are found in it.
Column Comment.11: PALEO OBSERVATION QUALIFIER ID: Unique identifier for this paleontologicalqualifier. These are further constrained by a qualifier type. A qualifier that is added toan identification of a fossil or its interpretation. Can include values such as AT, IN etc.
Column Comment.12: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.13: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.14: FROM RELATIVE STRAT NAME SET IDENTIFIER: a component of the uniqueidentifier for the stratigraphic unit that is the starting point for the chronlogicalequivalent of the assemblage identified.
Column Comment.15: FROM RELATIVE STRAT UNIT IDENTIFIER: a component of the unique identifierfor the stratigraphic unit that is the starting point for the chronlogical equivalent of theassemblage identified.
Column Comment.16: FROM STRATIGRAPHIC NAME SET IDENTIFIER: Part of the primary key for thestarting point of the stratigraphic unit that is represented by this detail portion of thesummary.
Column Comment.17: FROM STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: Part of the primary key for the startingpoint of the stratigraphic unit that is represented by this detail portion of the summary.
Column Comment.18: PALEO INTERPRETATION TYPE: the type of interpreted inforamtion contained,such as an age boundary, change boundary, age zone etc.
Column Comment.19: LITHOLOGY TYPE: This reference table describes the major lithologic types. Forexample sandstone, limestone, dolomite or shale.
Column Comment.20: LITHOLOGIC STRUCTURE: Type of sedimentary or other rock structure occurring inthe lithologic interval being described (e.g., cross-stratification, mud cracks, ripplemarks, etc.). The rock structure may be non-sedimentary, such as contorted beddingor fault zone.
Column Comment.21: MATURATION OBSERVATION NUMBER: Unique obs no assigned to a maturationstudy.
Column Comment.22: CONFIDENCE IDENTIFER A Unique identifier for the code associated withconfidence of a paleontological event or pick, such as positive, doubtful etc. In somecompanies, numeric codes are assigned.
Column Comment.23: PALEO OBSERVATION QUALIFIER ID: Unique identifier for this paleontologicalqualifier. These are further constrained by a qualifier type. A qualifier that is added toan identification of a fossil or its interpretation. Can include values such as AT, IN etc.
Column Comment.24: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.25: PREFERRED INDICATOR: a Y/N flag indicating that this row of data is to be used bydefault for reports etc.
Column Comment.26: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.27: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.28: THERMAL ALTERATION INDEX: One of various indices employed to determinewhat temperature the rock has attained during its history. For example, a conodontalteration index uses the changes in color which occur in its apatitic composition todetermine the temperatures reached, and assess the rocks thermal maturation.
Column Comment.29: TOP MEASURED DEPTH: the upper measured depth for this detail record.
Column Comment.31: TO RELATIVE STRAT NAME SET IDENTIFIER: a component of the unique identifierfor the stratigraphic unit that is the ending point for the chronlogical equivalent of theassemblage identified.
Column Comment.32: TO RELATIVE STRAT UNIT IDENTIFIER: a component of the unique identifier forthe stratigraphic unit that is the ending point for the chronlogical equivalent of theassemblage identified.
Column Comment.33: TO STRATIGRAPHIC NAME SET IDENTIFIER: Part of the primary key for theending point of the stratigraphic unit that is represented by this detail portion of thesummary.
Column Comment.34: TO STRATIGRAPHIC UNIT IDENTIFIER: Part of the primary key for the ending pointof the stratigraphic unit that is represented by this detail portion of the summary.
Column Comment.35: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.36: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.37: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.38: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.39: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.40: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.41: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
